50|$|Banfield joined CNN in January 2012 as co-anchor with Zoraida Sambolin, of the network's morning show, Early Start. On August 13, 2012, Banfield {{moved to}} the 11 a.m. edition of CNN Newsroom in New York each weekday, {{replacing}} <b>Kyra</b> <b>Phillips</b> as anchor. On August 6, 2013, {{it was announced that}} CNN would rebrand its 11 a.m. hour of CNN Newsroom. The show, called Legal View with Ashleigh Banfield, aired at 12 noon Eastern. In 2014, Banfield was featured in a small role portraying herself in the Netflix series House of Cards. OctoberBanfield joined CNN sister station HLN as host on the legal issues interview program Primetime Justice with Ashleigh Banfield, which airs at 8 p.m. Monday to Thursday.|$|E
